Subject: Re: [T2] Fuel cut off

Just shows what can happen whenever you try to "improve" a stock system. 
You don't know the results of an experiment until you run it and see what 
happens.

Try this. Before shutting off the motor, hit the fuel cutoff and let it 
idle for a minute or so. That should leave the float valve open to relieve 
any residual pressure buildup.

At 06:23 PM 02/09/2003, you wrote:

