>I have installed a solenoid cut off in the fuel line

>when I turn it
>off the pressure has risen to as high as 12psi.

>  What this now does is make it MUCH more likely to push a
>hose off, or burst an old line. So just beware. I'm now wondering how to
>relive this pressure!!
